==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|it|en}} {{term|Sicilia|lang=it}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|Sicilia||lang=la}}, from {{etyl|grc|en}} {{term|Σικελία||tr=Sikelia|lang=grc|sc=polytonic}}, from {{term|Σίκελος||{{w|Sicels}}|tr=Sikelos|lang=grc}}, the name of an ancient, indigenous people on the Tiber.

===Proper noun===
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-proper noun|Sicilies}} {{qualifier|see Usage notes below}}

# An autonomous region and island of [[Italy]].

====Usage notes====
* While the rules of English state that proper nouns ending in ''y'' add an ''s'' to form their plural (as in ''[[Germany]]s'' and ''[[Mary]]s''), ''Sicily'' is an exception to this rule, as in ''[[w:Kingdom of the Two Sicilies|The Kingdom of the Two Sicilies]]''.

